		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/512</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently the Scons build uses the -Werror gcc flag by default.  This is not friendly 
to developers who are using newer versions of gcc (e.g. from new Ubuntu/Debian 
releases), because new versions of gcc tend to introduce new warnings which can break 
the build.

Furthermore, -Werror is hard-coded into the Scons build.  There should at least be an 
option to omit it, which should be easy to find.  Ideally, -Werror should be omitted by 
default, as in most open source projects.

gdb's autoconf scripts also pass -Werror by default, which can cause the toolchain 
build with newer gcc versions (even for those people who don't need gdb).
